text: hey g'day guys wayne perkins here just uh come down to have a look at this react pump it's down the bottom of new zealand windham and southland uh it's a ripper day but it always is down in southland so um gary got the chair going we sent it to him um i think around about june uh he's running mainly for the winter it's for his uh block up just got to pump water about 110 metres up the hill uh for his cattle and so really just needs it in the winter so it's not running today um so what he did he's got a four panel system which is an 11 20 watt system it's got them set up there across the road so you can get good sun um cable and come down he's dug the cable under the road pumps down here we've got about a two meter suction lift from um a good source down there and it's um yeah it's been a good result pumping hundred meters up two meter suction lift four panel system giving a good good quantities of water uh the pump's going well we're really proud of this pump and look if you're if you're looking for something on your farm if you you need to push water up a hill and uh you know you've got no power around and you're interested in some solar give us a call you know the react pump it's going pretty well there's some people out there pretty happy with it and i'd love to talk to you cheers
